main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Wall, Michigan on September 6, 1956, involving one object that was tracked visually and on ground radar.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 15-20 feet in diameter and circular in shape,It was cream to orange in color and reached speeds of approximately 400-500 mph,The object exhibited erratic maneuvers, with sudden starts and stops,The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes and the object disappeared into the overcast sky,The pilot of an F-89 jet reported seeing the object while on an intercept mission.
witness description: Pilot of the F-89 jets on intercept mission
